Rumor has spread that Afghanistan has immense resources.
This adds to the impression that the Western countries were only there to seize it.
Without energy to process the iron or copper ore on site, or without means of transport for export over the mountains, mining is not possible.
The Chinese have almost left the Mes Aynak copper mine, the international archaeologists (funded by the World Bank) are making their excavations on the huge Buddhist site and remain the province’s most important employers.
One day it will also be necessary for Afghanistan and Pakistan, on which imports and exports are largely dependent, to restore normal relations.
