It is not used to calculate the object depth.
More cameras could potentially solve the problem...
Or worsen the problem, as more calculations would be needed.
It would be nice to have a flexible, Kinect-like system where we could play with different camera inclinations to see how that helps us determine a position in three dimensions.
- If I remember correctly, unlike Google, Microsoft did not present its glasses to the public.
Don’t you think that when it comes to applying the technology of augmented reality in everyday life, glasses have the best prospects?
- Of course, it is not pleasant to always hold a smartphone in the raised hand on the go, but I think this: the best variant would be a "changing" extended reality, where we could switch from glasses to the smartphone via a cloud,
