<0xC5><0xA0>imon Ornest: At our concerts we want to collect positive energy
What do you think about the end of the world in less than a month?
This is one of those disaster reports that we humans like to respond to.
With our band The Tap Tap, we are more likely to make fun of it and say that we are the only band in the world that can collect enough positive energy to stop or prevent the end of the world.
In December you will also realize a unique project with three concerts against the end of the world.
Can you introduce the project to our readers?
This is a national charity event that we have been planning for two years.
For this, we want to use the marketing potential of the Mayan calendar, whose end is predicted for December 21 at 11:10 a.m.
The day before, i.e. on 20 December, three concerts will take place simultaneously in Prague, Brno and Ostrava from 21:00.
The end of the concerts is supposed to be about the time when the Mayan calendar ends on the Pacific island of Kiribati, which is in a 12-hour time zone ahead of us.
From whom does this idea come?
Originally probably from me, then we designed the idea together with our graphic designer Honza Augusta.
Not only do we want to gather enough positive energy to prevent the end of the world, but we also want to think together with the public about the state in which we once hand this world over to our children.
On the occasion of the end of the Mayan calendar, we have also developed a unique collection of shoes, t-shirts, bags and keyrings against the end of the world, which people can also support with their purchase through www.e-tap.cz.
The Tap Tap has also recorded, together with other performers, the so-called anthem against the end of the world with the title "Weltuntergang fällt aus".
Today, the anthem is already very popular on YouTube. Will it also be heard at the charity concerts?
Of course, and at the very end, provided that everything works out and the end of the world does not happen...
The anthem will be sung by all performers at all three concerts simultaneously.
In addition, the hymns will be broadcast live together in a direct circuit from Czech TV.
The text of the hymn comes from Tomá<0xC5><0xA1> Hanák, who also plays the main character of Jesus in the video clip, also Xindl X sings with...
How did you come to work with both?
We also cooperate with other personalities of the Czech cultural scene, which is related to the fact that we organize many charity events and concerts...
We make every effort to get these people involved in our projects.
It turned out that most people are interested in working with us and enjoying it.
What is the purpose of the proceeds of the concerts against the end of the world?
For the establishment of the accessible educational centre Studeo, on which we have been working for six years together with the association Tap in the Jedli<0xC4><0x8D>ka Institute.
Students of the Jedli<0xC4><0x8D>ka Institute are regularly supervised by editors who help them with various leisure activities.
Since the students themselves do not have the means to visit the editors, we would like to help them in this way.
As part of the completion of the Jedli<0xC4><0x8D>ka Institute, a separate building will be built, into which we will move with this project.
At each concert, several groups and performers perform.
